-- Popolare Vicenza says plans takeover bid on Banca Etruria 
-- By Francesca Landini and Gianluca Semeraro
-- Thu May 29, 2014 01:47AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, May 29 (Reuters) - Italian mid-sized lender Banca Popolare di Vicenza [BPVIC.UL] said on Thursday it was ready to launch a takeover bid on smaller rival Banca Etruria <PEL.MI>.

The offer would be in cash, at a price of 1 euro per share, with a premium of 25.8 percent on Wednesday's closing for Banca Etruria shares, the lender said in a statement.